⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Room 101
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦Room 101:1984:cdea71⟧

WHO   — Room 101 — the worst thing in the world
WHAT  — The instrument of total breaking: it does not seek confession but the destruction of the self's last loyalty.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the regime's aim is the soul — and the soul breaks not at pain in general but at <i>your</i> particular terror.
HOW   — By the worst thing in the world, tailored to the prisoner (for Winston, the rats), used to make him betray Julia.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the worst thing in the world, and it is different for everyone — and the moment you beg me to do it to someone you love, you are remade.

